One way to approach this is by identifying core principles or values that different philosophies already share, such as concepts of justice, well-being, or truth. From there, a structured dialogue can be set up where each viewpoint articulates its understanding of these core values, identifying areas of overlap and difference. The goal is to foster mutual recognition of these values' significance, even if the justifications differ, creating a foundation for common ground.

